data: Based on the given data, freelancers in Canada have the highest average income at $5273.79 USD, while those in the Middle East have the lowest at $4817.76 USD. The difference in income between these two regions is $456.03 USD. Freelancers in Asia have the next highest average income at $5120.55 USD, which is $152.83 USD higher than the UK's average income of $4921.01 USD. The smallest difference in average income is between Australia and the US, with a difference of only $107.90 USD.
